-- Global Funds Buy Net 16.4 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2012-06-28T03:28:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-28/global-funds-buy-net-16-4-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors  bought a  net 16.4
billion rupees ($288 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 0.8 percent to 948.7 billion rupees, or 33
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 861 million rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
